insert  into `wp_posts`(`ID`,`post_author`,`post_date`,`post_date_gmt`,`post_content`,`post_title`,`post_excerpt`,`post_status`,`comment_status`,`ping_status`,`post_password`,`post_name`,`to_ping`,`pinged`,`post_modified`,`post_modified_gmt`,`post_content_filtered`,`post_parent`,`guid`,`menu_order`,`post_type`,`post_mime_type`,`comment_count`) values (258,1,'2011-06-25 07:47:15','2011-06-25 07:47:15','In 1994, I came to this country carrying a VIP (remember that brand from India?) suitcase, smaller than my daughter’s school bag. I had nothing but a H1b visa to work as a software engineer at Microsoft Corporation in Seattle and tons of dreams in my eyes.\r\n\r\nToday, I am father of two wonderful daughters, married for the last 11 years. I am settled with a mortgage in the Bay area.  In typical Silicon Valley fashion, I have seen it all – the rise, the burst, the garage start-ups, the global conglomerates.\r\n\r\nIn a not-so-glamorous moments of life,  as I rumbled through my garage, I painfully realized something – all my dreams neatly tucked away in pictures, scrap books, documents &amp; hand-paintings, are slowly dying. Paper has an age – if the rodents don’t get to it sooner. I just could not bear that sight and knew that I need to save these papers for posterity. I quickly made a jaunt to the nearby Fry’s and bought myself a very nice scanner.\r\n\r\nAnd that’s when it hit me – I may not be the lonely person with this problem. Doing some quick “market research” by making some phone calls to friends around, I started to realize the magnitude and commonality of the problem. After mulling over it for days, I decided to launch, Skannr.com, a site dedicated to helping us preserve our memorabilia.','About','','inherit','open','open','','9-revision-5','','','2011-06-25 07:47:15','2011-06-25 07:47:15','',9,'http://www.clusterstogo.com/9-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0);
